6	//         listing:          <row from public.listings>,
7	//         conditions:       <rows from listing_conditions, both kinds>,
8	//         sample_videos:    <rows from sample_videos>,
9	//         eligibility: {
10	//           eligible:                boolean,
11	//           failed_conditions:       Array<{metric, platform, required, actual}>,
12	//           has_active_application:  boolean,
13	//         }
14	//       }
15	//     → 400 { error: 'INVALID_JSON' | 'INVALID_REQUEST' }
16	//     → 401 { error: 'UNAUTHORIZED' }
17	//     → 403 { error: 'FORBIDDEN' }       // non-creator role
18	//     → 404 { error: 'LISTING_NOT_FOUND' } // also covers draft/archived listings
19	//     → 500 { error: 'SERVER_MISCONFIGURED' | 'DB_ERROR' }
20	//
21	// Auth: Marketify JWT (HS256, MARKETIFY_JWT_SECRET). Verifies via
22	//       _shared/jwt.ts and asserts role='creator'. Deployed with
23	//       verify_jwt=false at the gateway because the gateway only knows
24	//       about Supabase's own JWT secret — the handler enforces auth.
25	//
26	// Response shape — primary reference is docs/tech-architecture.md §5.4
27	// (spec is authoritative per the Ralph iteration rules). Two deltas vs
28	// the US-039 story AC, both driven by §5.4:
29	//   1. `conditions` is a single array — the client splits by `kind`.
30	//      The story's `pre_conditions` / `post_conditions` split contradicts
31	//      §5.4's single `conditions: ListingCondition[]` field.
32	//   2. `eligibility.failed_conditions` is `Array<{metric, required, actual}>`
33	//      — the story's `reasons: string[]` contradicts §5.4. We also keep
34	//      `platform` as an additive disambiguator because `min_followers`
35	//      would otherwise be ambiguous across TikTok/Instagram; §5.4 is
36	//      under-specified on the item shape and an additive field is not
37	//      a structural departure.
38	//
39	// Eligibility — only PRE conditions gate apply-time eligibility per
40	// docs/tech-architecture.md §6.3 ("Pre-conditions: evaluated on all
41	// posts; post-conditions: evaluated on submissions"). POST conditions
42	// are returned in `conditions` for the UI to display but do not
43	// contribute to `eligible` / `failed_conditions`.
44	//
45	// Fail-closed on missing metrics (§3d): when the creator hasn't been
46	// scraped yet (or a specific platform field is NULL), the PRE condition
47	// keyed on that field fails — the spec calls this out explicitly for
48	// Instagram `min_avg_views_last_n` ("Listings that require … treat null
49	// as ineligible (fail-closed).") and we apply the same rule uniformly.
50	// The same rule extends to pre-condition rows with an unknown operator
51	// or unreadable metric: treat as failed rather than silently passing,
52	// so a future mis-migrated row can't flip a listing to eligible by
53	// accident.
54	//
